"English: probably also a variant of   Hatch  , with voicing of the final consonant.","Americanized form (translation into English) of German   Hecke  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hatch","meanings":["English: habitational name from Hatch (Bedfordshire, Devon, Hampshire, Somerset, Wiltshire), Hacche in South Molton (Devon), or else a topographic name from residence near a hatch, a gate leading to a forest or sometimes a sluice-gate, from Middle English <i>hacche</i> ‘gate’ (Old English <i>hæcce</i>, Kentish Old English <i>hec(c)</i>). This name has been in Ireland since the 17th century, associated with County Meath and the nearby part of Louth."]},{"name":"Hedges","meanings":["English: variant of   Hedge  , from the plural or, with excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Hedger","meanings":["English (southeastern): occupational name from Middle English <i>heg(g)er</i> ‘hedger, a maker or repairer of hedges’, or perhaps in some cases a topographic name for a ‘dweller by the hedge’; compare   Hedge  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Hedge was born in 1460, in Suffolk, England as the son of Stevin Hedge. He had at least 1 son with Bridget. He died in 1543, in England, at the age of 83, and was buried in Sandwich, Kent, England."},"et":{"1460–1543":"1460–1543","1460–Female":"1460–Surnud","1473–1573":"1473–1573","–Male":"Surnud","14 September 1543":"14. september 1543","1543":"1543","1573":"1573","1473":"1473","1460":"1460","England":"England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Sandwich, Kent, England":"Sandwich, Kent, England","East Bergholt, Babergh district, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"East Bergholt, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1460–1543":"1460–1543","1460–Female":"1460–Kuollut","1473–1573":"1473–1573","–Male":"Kuollut","14 September 1543":"14. syyskuut